#Configure a Jenkins pipeline to automate the building and deployment of a Dockerized application from GitHub


Step 1 – Create Jenkins persistent volume
docker volume create jenkins-data
Output
jenkins-data

Step 2 – Start Jenkins container
For Linux/macOS
docker run -d \  --name jenkins \  -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 \  -v jenkins-data:/var/jenkins_home \  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \  jenkins/jenkins:lts
For Windows CMD, use one line
docker run -d --name jenkins -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 -v jenkins-data:/var/jenkins_home -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock jenkins/jenkins:lts

Check container

docker ps
Output
You should see a container named jenkins running.

Step 3 – Get Jenkins initial admin password
docker exec jenkins cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword
Output
You will get a long password like:
a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8...
Copy this password.

Step 4 – Open Jenkins in browser
Open:
http://localhost:8080


Paste the admin password


Click Continue


Choose Install suggested plugins


Wait for installation


Create admin user


Finish setup



Step 5 – Install Docker Pipeline plugin
In Jenkins:


Go to Manage Jenkins


Go to Plugins


Search for Docker Pipeline


Install it



Step 6 – Install Docker CLI inside Jenkins container
docker exec -u root jenkins bash -c "apt-get update && apt-get install -y docker.io"
