Result
The Jenkins pipeline was configured successfully to automate cloning from GitHub, building the Docker image, pushing it to Docker Hub, and deploying the Dockerized application.

Viva answer
Jenkins pipeline automates CI/CD. It pulls code from GitHub, builds a Docker image using the Dockerfile, pushes the image to Docker Hub using stored credentials, and deploys the container automatically.
Important note for Windows
If Docker socket mount /var/run/docker.sock does not work on your system, Jenkins may fail to run Docker commands. In that case, send the exact error from Jenkins Console Output and I will give the fix for your machine.
